#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:5.1"
msgid "2. Udosita(dutiyakathina)sikkhāpada"
msgstr "2. The training rule on outbuildings"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.198"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1883"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.3"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks stored one of their robes with other monks and then left to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.5"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni ciraṃ nikkhittāni kaṇṇakitāni honti."
msgstr "Because they were stored for a long time, the robes became moldy."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.6"
msgid "Tāni bhikkhū otāpenti."
msgstr "The monks put them out in the sun."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.7"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā ānando senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto te bhikkhū tāni cīvarāni otāpente."
msgstr "While inspecting the dwellings, Venerable Ānanda saw the monks sunning those robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.8"
msgid "Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "He asked them,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.10"
msgid "“kassimāni, āvuso, cīvarāni kaṇṇakitānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Whose moldy robes are these?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.11"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they told him what had happened."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.12"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:6.13"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can those monks store one of their robes with other monks and then leave to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1884"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, Venerable Ānanda informed the Master. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are acting in this way?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.13"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā bhikkhūnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissanti."
msgstr "How can these foolish men store one of their robes with other monks and then leave to travel the countryside with a lower and an upper robe?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:7.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:8.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1885"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:8.2"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine ekarattampi ce bhikkhu ticīvarena vippavaseyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if a monk stays apart from his three robes even for a single day, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1886"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:9.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.199"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1887"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosambiyaṃ gilāno hoti."
msgstr "At one time a certain monk in Kosambī was sick."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.3"
msgid "Ñātakā tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr "The relatives of that monk sent him a message:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.4"
msgid "“āgacchatu bhadanto, mayaṃ, upaṭṭhahissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, we will attend on you.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.14"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.5"
msgid "Bhikkhūpi evamāhaṃsu—“gacchāvuso, ñātakā taṃ upaṭṭhahissantī”ti."
msgstr "Other monks urged him to go, "

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.6"
msgid "So evamāha—"
msgstr "but he said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.7"
msgid "“bhagavatāvuso, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.8"
msgid "‘na ticīvarena vippavasitabban’ti."
msgstr "that you cannot be apart from your three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.9"
msgid "Ahañcamhi gilāno."
msgstr "Because I am sick,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.10"
msgid "Na sakkomi ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to travel with all three robes,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.11"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "and therefore I cannot go.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.12"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They informed the Master."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.14"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ dātuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to give permission to a sick monk to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā."
msgstr "And it should be given in this way."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.16"
msgid "Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, the sick monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.17"
msgid "‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno."
msgstr "‘Venerables, I’m sick."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.18"
msgid "Na sakkomi ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to travel with my three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.19"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti."
msgstr "I ask the Order for permission to stay apart from my three robes.’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.20"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "And he should ask a second"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.21"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:10.22"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1888"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.1"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.3"
msgid "Na sakkoti ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "He is not able to travel with his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.4"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for permission to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.5"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ dadeyya."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:11.6"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1889"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.15"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.1"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.3"
msgid "Na sakkoti ticīvaraṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "He is not able to travel with his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.4"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for permission to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.5"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiṃ deti."
msgstr "The Order gives permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.6"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of giving permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three robes should remain silent."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:12.7"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1890"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:13.1"
msgid "Dinnā saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno ticīvarena avippavāsasammuti."
msgstr "The Order has given permission to monk so-and-so to stay apart from his three robes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:13.2"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:13.3"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1891"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:14.1"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:15.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1892"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:15.2"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine ekarattampi ce bhikkhu ticīvarena vippavaseyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if a monk stays apart from his three robes even for a single day, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:15.3"
msgid "(<em>2</em>:<strong>21</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:16.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1893"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:16.2"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>This refers to robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:16.3"
msgctxt "bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā vā upacchinnā."
msgstr "the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1894"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:17.1"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>For an explanation of this see <span class="ref">Mv.7.1.7</span> and <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:17.2"
msgctxt "aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr "it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended it, whichever comes first."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1895"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:18.1"
msgid "Ekarattampi ce bhikkhu ticīvarena vippavaseyyāti"
msgstr "If a monk stays apart from his three robes even for a single day:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:18.2"
msgctxt "saṅghāṭiyā vā uttarāsaṅgena vā antaravāsakena vā."
msgstr "from the outer robe, from the upper robe, or from the lower robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1896"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:19.1"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:19.2"
msgctxt "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.200"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1897"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.1"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ hotīti"
msgstr "Entailing relinquishment:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.2"
msgctxt "saha aruṇuggamanā nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "entailing relinquishment at dawn."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to the Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pi-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.16"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.6"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ rattivippavutthaṃ aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe which I have stayed apart from for one day without the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.7"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:20.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.3"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1898"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.4"
msgid "Gāmo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "A village may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.5"
msgid "Nivesanaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a house may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.6"
msgid "Udosito ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "an outbuilding may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.7"
msgid "Aṭṭo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a watchtower may have a single entrance or many;"

#. <span class="note" hidden>I have here included three kinds of building—the <i lang="pi">māḷa</i>, the <i lang="pi">pāsāda</i>, and the <i lang="pi">hammiya</i>—into one category, “stilt house.” See below for an explanation.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.8"
msgid "Māḷo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a stilt house may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.9"
msgid "Pāsādo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.10"
msgid "Hammiyaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.17"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.11"
msgid "Nāvā ekūpacārā nānūpacārā."
msgstr "a boat may have a single entrance or many;"

#. <span class="note" hidden>The Pali term <i lang="pi">upacāra</i> may mean ‘entrance’ or ‘neighborhood,’ and thus I vary the translation depending on the context.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.12"
msgid "Sattho ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a caravan may have a single neighborhood or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.13"
msgid "Khettaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a field may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.14"
msgid "Dhaññakaraṇaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "a threshing floor may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.15"
msgid "Ārāmo ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a park may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.16"
msgid "Vihāro ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "a monastery may have a single entrance or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.17"
msgid "Rukkhamūlaṃ ekūpacāraṃ nānūpacāraṃ."
msgstr "the foot of a tree may have a single neighborhood or many;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:21.18"
msgid "Ajjhokāso ekūpacāro nānūpacāro."
msgstr "out in the open may have a single neighborhood or many."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1899"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.2"
msgid "Gāmo ekūpacāro nāma"
msgstr "A village with a single entrance"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.3"
msgctxt "ekakulassa gāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "means it is an enclosed village belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.4"
msgid "Antogāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antogāme vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the village, one must stay within the village."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.5"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "If the village is not enclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.18"></a>
#. <span class="note" hidden>“Of the house” is added from the commentary, see <span class="ref">Sp.3.652.20</span>. Without this explanation it is hard to make out whether the arm’s reach is from the house or from the robe. In each instance below I have added the commentarial explanation, found at <span class="ref">Sp.3.652.20-3.655.10</span>, so as to make it clear what the arm’s reach relates to.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:22.6"
msgid "yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the house where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1900"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.1"
msgid "Nānākulassa gāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed village belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.653.6</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.2"
msgid "Yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ sabhāye vā dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in a house, one must stay in that house, in the meeting hall, or at the gateway to the village, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the meeting hall or the gateway."

#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.653.14</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.3"
msgid "Sabhāyaṃ gacchantena hatthapāse cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā sabhāye vā vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If one puts aside the robe within arm’s reach while going to the meeting hall, one must stay in the meeting hall, or at the gateway to the village, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.msgstr "3.653.29</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.4"
msgid "Sabhāye cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā sabhāye vā vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If the robe is kept in the meeting hall, one must stay in the meeting hall, or at the gateway to the village, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.5"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:23.6"
msgid "yasmiṃ ghare cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ghare vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the house where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1901"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:24.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa nivesanaṃ hoti parikkhittañca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed house belonging to one clan and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:24.2"
msgid "Antonivesane cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antonivesane vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the house, one must stay within the house."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:24.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.7</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:24.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1902"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:25.1"
msgid "Nānākulassa nivesanaṃ hoti parikkhittañca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed house belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.19"></a><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi">Dvāramūle</i>. Explained by the commentary as “at the base of that door of the house which is common to all,” <i lang="pi">sabbesaṃ sādhāraṇe gharadvāramūle</i>, <span class="ref">Sp.3.654.8</span>.</span>
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.9</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:25.2"
msgid "Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in a room, one must stay in that room, or at the main entrance, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:25.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:25.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.201"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1903"></a><strong class="term">
#. <span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi">Uddosita</i>. Explained in the commentary as “a hall for goods such as vehicles, etc,” <i lang="pi">yānādīnaṃ bhaṇḍānaṃ sālā</i>, see <span class="ref">Sp.3.654.10</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:26.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa udosito hoti parikkhitto ca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed outbuilding belonging to one clan and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:26.2"
msgid "Antoudosite cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoudosite vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the building, one must stay within the building."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:26.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.11</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:26.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1904"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:27.1"
msgid "Nānākulassa udosito hoti parikkhitto ca, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "An enclosed outbuilding belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.11</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:27.2"
msgid "Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in a room, one must stay in that room, or at the main entrance, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:27.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.11</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:27.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1905"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:28.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa aṭṭo hoti,"
msgstr "A watchtower belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:28.2"
msgid "antoaṭṭe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoaṭṭe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the watchtower, one must stay within the watchtower."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:28.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa aṭṭo hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "A watchtower belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:28.4"
msgid "Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or at the main entrance, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1906"></a><strong class="term">
#. <span class="note" hidden>The building in <span class="ref">MS.1.1906</span>, the <i lang="pi">māḷa</i>, is hard to distinguish from the buildings mentioned in the next two paragraphs, the <i lang="pi">pāsāda</i> and the <i lang="pi">hammiya</i>. In fact the commentary says they are all different types of <i lang="pi">pāsāda</i>, that is, different kinds of “stilt houses,” see <span class="ref">Sp.3.654.11</span>. What all these buildings have in common—and this is what distinguishes them from the buildings in <span class="ref">MS.1.1901-1.1904</span>, the <i lang="pi">nivesana</i> and the <i lang="pi">udosita</i>—is that they do not have an enclosed category. Rather than try, from a modern perspecitve, the probably futile task of naming each of these buildings, which in any case would not be very useful from a practical perspective, I have instead grouped them together as “stilt house.” For why a <i lang="pi">pāsāda</i> is a stilt house, see [ref. to internet page].</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:29.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa māḷo hoti,"
msgstr "A stilt house belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:29.2"
msgid "antomāḷe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antomāḷe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept in the stilt house, one must stay within the stilt house."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:29.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa māḷo hoti nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā,"
msgstr "A stilt house belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:29.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or at the main entrance, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1907"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:30.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa pāsādo hoti,"
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:30.2"
msgid "antopāsāde cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antopāsāde vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:30.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa pāsādo hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:30.4"
msgid "Yasmiṃ gabbhe cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ gabbhe vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1908"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:31.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa hammiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:31.2"
msgid "Antohammiye cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antohammiye vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:31.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa hammiyaṃ hoti, nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
