#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.10"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1909"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:32.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa nāvā hoti."
msgstr "A boat belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:32.2"
msgid "Antonāvāya cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antonāvāya vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept on the boat, one must stay on the boat."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:32.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa nāvā hoti nānāgabbhā nānāovarakā."
msgstr "A boat belonging to many clans and having many rooms:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:32.4"
msgid "Yasmiṃ ovarake cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ ovarake vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the room where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the room."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1910"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:33.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa sattho hoti."
msgstr "A caravan belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>According to the commentary, an <i lang="pi">abbhantara</i> is equivalent to 28 <i lang="pi">hatthas</i> (<span class="ref">Sp.3.654.16</span>). Following the estimate of the <i lang="pi">hattha</i> in BMC I, pp.565-566, as 50 centimeters, this gives 14 metes for the <i lang="pi">abbhantara</i> or about 100 meters for 7 <i lang="pi">abbhantaras</i>.</span>
#. <span class="note" hidden>That is one <i lang="pi">abbhantara</i>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:33.2"
msgid "Satthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā purato vā pacchato vā sattabbhantarā na vijahitabbā, passato abbhantaraṃ na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the caravan, one must not go further than 100 meters in front of or behind the caravan, and no further than 14 meters from either side."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:33.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa sattho hoti,"
msgstr "A caravan belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp-ṭ.2.489</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:33.4"
msgid "satthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the caravan, one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the caravan."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1911"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa khettaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed field belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.2"
msgid "Antokhette cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antokhette vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the field, one must stay within that field."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.26</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa khettaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed field belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.27</span>.<span class="ref">Sp-t.2.490</span> states that staying within arm’s reach of the robe is also acceptable. The same holds for the next two categories of threshing floor and park.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.6"
msgid "Antokhette cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the field, one must stay at the entrance to the field, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.7"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.654.28</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:34.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1912"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa dhaññakaraṇaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed threshing floor belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.2"
msgid "Antodhaññakaraṇe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antodhaññakaraṇe vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept on the threshing floor, one must stay on that threshing floor."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.3"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>For the threshing floor and the next category of park, arm’s reach has the same meaning as for field, see <span class="ref">Sp.3.655.1</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa dhaññakaraṇaṃ hoti parikkhittañca."
msgstr "An enclosed threshing floor belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.21"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.6"
msgid "Antodhaññakaraṇe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept on the threshing floor, one must stay at the entrance to the threshing floor, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.7"
msgid "Aparikkhittaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:35.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1913"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa ārāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed park belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.2"
msgid "Antoārāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antoārāme vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the park, one must stay within that park."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa ārāmo hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed park belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.6"
msgid "Antoārāme cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā dvāramūle vā vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the park, one must stay at the entrance to the park, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the entrance or the robe."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.7"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:36.8"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.202"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1914"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa vihāro hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed monastery belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.2"
msgid "Antovihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antovihāre vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the monastery, one must stay within that monastery."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.3"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.655.2</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.4"
msgid "yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of that dwelling."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.5"
msgid "Nānākulassa vihāro hoti parikkhitto ca."
msgstr "An enclosed monastery belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ dvāramūle vā, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or at the main entrance to the monastery, or not go beyond arm’s reach of either."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.7"
msgid "Aparikkhitto hoti,"
msgstr "It is unenclosed:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:37.8"
msgid "yasmiṃ vihāre cīvaraṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti tasmiṃ vihāre vatthabbaṃ, hatthapāsā vā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must stay in the monastic dwelling where the robe is kept, or not go beyond arm’s reach of the dwelling."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1915"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:38.1"
msgid "Ekakulassa rukkhamūlaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "The foot of a tree belonging to one clan:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:38.2"
msgid "yaṃ majjhanhike kāle samantā chāyā pharati, antochāyāya cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā antochāyāya vatthabbaṃ."
msgstr "if the robe is kept within the area of the midday shadow of the tree, one must stay within that area."

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:38.3"
msgid "Nānākulassa rukkhamūlaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "The foot of a tree belonging to many clans:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden><span class="ref">Sp.3.655.9</span>.</span>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:38.4"
msgid "hatthapāsā na vijahitabbaṃ."
msgstr "one must not go beyond arm’s reach of the robe."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1916"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:39.1"
msgid "Ajjhokāso ekūpacāro nāma"
msgstr "Out in the open with one neighborhood:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>That is, 7 <i lang="pi">abbhantaras</i>. According to the commentary, an <i lang="pi">abbhantara</i> is equivalent to 28 <i lang="pi">hatthas</i> (<span class="ref">Sp.3.654.16</span>). Following the estimate of the <i lang="pi">hattha</i> in BMC I, pp.565-566, as 50 centimeters, this gives 14 metes for the <i lang="pi">abbhantara</i> or about 100 meters for 7 <i lang="pi">abbhantaras</i>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:39.2"
msgid "agāmake araññe samantā sattabbhantarā ekūpacāro,"
msgstr "in the wilderness, where there is no habitation, one neighborhood is the area covered by a circle with radius 100 meters."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.22"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:39.3"
msgid "tato paraṃ nānūpacāro."
msgstr "</span><strong class=\"term\">Many neighborhoods</strong>: <span class=\"gloss\">whatever lies beyond that."

#. </span>
#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1917"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.2"
msgid "Vippavutthe vippavutthasaññī aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he has stayed apart and he perceives that he has stayed apart, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.3"
msgid "Vippavutthe vematiko, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he has stayed apart, but he is unsure if he has, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.4"
msgid "Vippavutthe avippavutthasaññī, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he has stayed apart, but he perceives that he has not, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.23"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.5"
msgid "Appaccuddhaṭe paccuddhaṭasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If he has not relinquished the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.6"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr "If he has not given away the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.7"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If he has not lost the robe, but he perceives that he has, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.8"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If the robe is not destroyed, but he perceives that it is, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.9"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī"
msgstr "If the robe is not burnt, but he perceives that it is, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:40.10"
msgid "avilutte viluttasaññī, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the robe is not stolen, but he perceives that it is, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1918"></a><strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:41.1"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a robe which should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:41.2"
msgid "Avippavutthe vippavutthasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he has not stayed apart, but he perceives that he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:41.3"
msgid "Avippavutthe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he has not stayed apart, but he is unsure if he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:41.4"
msgid "Avippavutthe avippavutthasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If he has not stayed apart and he perceives that he has not stayed apart, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.2.3.19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1919"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.3"
msgid "antoaruṇe paccuddharati, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if before dawn it has been relinquished, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.4"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:42.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1920"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np2:43.1"
msgid "Udosita(dutiyakathina)sikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on outbuildings, is finished."

